{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdHDiebE9aZWii2QYyLen","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All 4 tests pass.\n\n**Root cause:** In `src/validate.js:7`, the domain regex used `(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*` — the `*` on the label body allowed a label to be **empty**, so a dot could be followed by nothing, i.e. a consecutive dot. That's why `user@mail..example.com` was accepted while mail to it bounces.\n\n**Fix:** Changed the label-content quantifier from `*` to `+`, requiring every domain label to be non-empty:\n\n```\n(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*  →  (\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]+)*\n```\n\n**Verification:** Added a failing test that reproduced the bounce (`user@mail..example.com` → now rejected) plus a guard that legitimate multi-label domains (`ada@mail.example.co.uk`) still pass. The reproduction failed before the fix and passes after; no existing tests broke.\n\nNote: the shipped test suite passed for months because it never exercised a consecutive-dot case — the two original tests only covered a plain address and a missing `@`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":366,"cache_read_input_tokens":28775,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":366},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6840c3c5-2206-47f0-a492-be7a1d52dc91","uuid":"a6562b80-2281-45a0-9366-dbc8d907f149","timestamp":"2026-07-22T14:02:53.086Z","request_id":"req_011CdHDiaTgWQGqxauZVTpWm"}
